<main class="about-page">
  <h1>About My8OSS</h1>

  <section class="about-intro">
    <p>
      My8OSS is an open software ecosystem focused on turning ideas into usable, production-ready systems.
    </p>
    <p>
      We don’t stay at the idea stage. We design, build, and ship software that is meant to be used, extended, and owned.
    </p>
    <p>
      “Once a Myth, Now My8OSS.” represents that transition from concept to execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-status">
    <h2>What we are</h2>
    <p>
      My8OSS is actively in development. It is a growing collection of tools, systems, and components that are being built in parallel toward a unified ecosystem.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is an engineering effort that is continuously shipping new parts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-principles">
    <h2>Core principles</h2>

    <p><strong>Open by default.</strong> Products are inspectable and modifiable.</p>

    <p><strong>Outcome alongside theory.</strong> We bridge shipping working systems with conceptual exploration.</p>

    <p><strong>Modular design.</strong> Each tool must function independently while contributing to a larger ecosystem.</p>

    <p><strong>Clarity in engineering.</strong> Software should be understandable, maintainable, and predictable.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-build">
    <h2>What we build</h2>

    <p>
      My8OSS spans multiple layers of software:
    </p>

    <p>
      • Lightweight applications and utilities<br/>
      • Developer tools and infrastructure components<br/>
      • System-level integrations and experiments<br/>
      • And more...
    </p>

    <p>
      Each project is developed independently, but designed to integrate into a larger structure over time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-contact">
    <h2>Get involved</h2>
    <p>
      Everything is developed openly on
      <a href="https://github.com/my8oss" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contributions, ideas, and experimentation are welcome as the ecosystem evolves.
    </p>
    <p>
      Explore the <a href="/docs">documentation</a> or check out the
      <a href="/apps">apps</a> currently in development.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>

